---
description: CSS appearance must stay Fluent UI/themed
globs: "**/*.css"
alwaysApply: false
---

# CSS appearance policy

- Avoid adding theme-dependent appearance in CSS (`color`, `background`, `border-color`, `box-shadow` colors, hover/active colors).
- Prefer Fluent UI `styles`/theming APIs in component code; let the active Fluent UI theme drive light/dark.
- If CSS is necessary, keep it theme-neutral (layout/spacing/positioning) and do not override Fluent UI component selectors.
- Do not use `!important` to win against Fluent UI styles.
- If you need a color, implement it via Fluent UI theme tokens (or existing Fluent UI-provided CSS variables), not hard-coded hex/rgb values.
- If you add styles which become orphaned, remove them.
